.TH man 3 "07 Dec 2021" "1.0" "simple_shell man page"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- hsh command interpreter (shell)

.SH SYNOPSIS
Is a command interpreter that reads lines from either path from

Command [options] [file]

.B Overview
the shell is a command interpreter that execute commands read from the line
of string, standart input or specified file, the program ensure that the
command is executed in the correct path.

.SH DESCRIPTION
hsh - is the standart command interpreter that is invoked for the 
system, receive a argument command to perform action, need a [option] to configurate
parameters for especial configurations, and files/directories to be displayed or manipulated 
, this version is 1.0.

.SH Return 
return 0 and display the command if is succeed, 1 or -1 if the program has someone error.

someone more has display: exit (0) if the exit succeed, exit (2) if the argument is number negative
and display other number with exit to terminate programm.
.br 
